cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL. 

The paper focuses on developing a novel neural layer for recognizing long-range activities in videos, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the properties of the proposed layer, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The experiments are conducted on video datasets, indicating that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) categories.
